<br>
When you sell your account, cancel your billing.  When the current pre-paid amount expires, they are forced to put in new billing information (thus not allowing charges for expansions and monthly service charges to the &quot;previous&quot; owner). <br>
<br>
Haven't we all seen this shit over and over again in the past 4½ years?  I can see how new people are making this mistake when purchasing (not saying this fucktard is green, btw), but the sellers really should know better, and how to keep it from happening.<br>
<br>
Now do you see why I don't condone selling accounts here?  Aside from it being against the EULA, it causes too many damn headaches.<br>
